<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD (Removal &#38; Reassembly)
        - VALVE LEVER REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="6">
        <title>VALVE LEVER REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If components become dislodged during service, reassemble the valve lever assembly component
                parts shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350309">3.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                , as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place the valve lever post onto the valve lever bolts, then insert the bolt head into a
                    1/2 in. socket,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350310">3.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . The bolt will align the post in the valve lever while the socket acts as a holding fixture.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>DURING VALVE LEVER ASSEMBLY, THE VALVE LEVER COMPONENTS MUST BE ASSEMBLIED IN THEIR
                            ORIGINAL LOCATION. DO NOT INTERMIX COMPONENTS.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4350308" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11056" filename="../figcg1/CG11056.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.8 Valve Lever Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350309" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10872" filename="../figcg1/CG10872.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.9 Valve Lever Assembly Components</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350310" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11010" filename="../figcg1/CG11010.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.10 Valve Lever Reassembly Step One</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place the valve lever over the post and bolt, which are held in place by the 1/2 in.
                    socket as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350311">3.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                    Then position the retainer over the post and lever.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a 3/4 in. socket over the retainer as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350312">3.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Strike the socket squarely using a plastic hammer to install the retainer onto the post.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Apply clean engine oil between the post and the valve lever.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Repeat steps a through c for the second valve lever and post on the assembly. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350310">3.10</hotlnk>
                        -
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350312">3.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                    Set aside the bolt and 1/2 in. socket.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">After both valve levers and valve lever posts are assembled, center the posts in the
                    retainer using a blade screwdriver, as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350313">3.13</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4350311" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11008" filename="../figcg1/CG11008.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.11 Valve Lever Reassembly Step Two</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350312" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11058" filename="../figcg1/CG11058.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.12 Valve Lever Reassembly Step Three</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350313" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11014" filename="../figcg1/CG11014.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.13 Post and Retainer Align Step Four</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
